{"title_page": "Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014)", "text_new": "{{short description|2014 Lucha Libre AAA World Wide event}}\n{{Infobox wrestling event\n|name=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014)\n|image=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014).jpg\n|caption=Promotional poster featuring various [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide|AAA]] wrestlers, including [[Myzteziz]] billed under his old ring name \"M\u00edstico\"\n|tagline=\n|promotion=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]]\n|date=June 7, 2014<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|attendance=7,000<ref>{{cite journal| last = Meltzer | first = Dave | authorlink = Dave Meltzer | date = June 16, 2014 | title = Jun 16 2014 Wrestling Observer Newsletter: Bryan stripped, how it happened, what was known, what happens next, UFC drug test issues and stories behind all of them, Super Juniors, WWE injury updates and contract talks, Rollins direction | journal = [[Dave Meltzer#Wrestling Observer Newsletter|Wrestling Observer Newsletter]] | location = [[Campbell, California]] | issn = 1083-9593 | page=15}}</ref>\n|venue=Plaza de Toros la Concordia<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|city=[[Orizaba]], [[Veracruz]]<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|liveevent=Y\n|lastevent=[[Rey de Reyes (2014)|Rey de Reyes]]\n|nextevent=[[Tripleman\u00eda XXII]]\n|event = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2011)|2011]]\n|nextevent2 = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2015)|2015]]\n}}\n'''Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014)''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for \"Summer of Scandal\") was a [[professional wrestling]] event produced by the [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] (AAA) [[professional wrestling promotion|promotion]], which took place on June 7, 2014, at Plaza de Toros la Concordia in [[Orizaba]], [[Veracruz]], [[Mexico]].<ref name=CardAAA>{{cite web | url = http://luchalibreaaa.com/carteleraaaa/item/1483-junio-7-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo-plaza-de-toros-la-concordia-orizaba-veracruz.html | title = Junio 7 - Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo: Plaza de Toros La Concordia, Orizaba, Veracruz | accessdate=June 8, 2014 | work=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] | language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=CardPWI>{{cite web | url = http://www.pwinsider.com/article/86046/the-lucha-report.html?p=1 | title = The Lucha Report | last=Zellner | first=Kris | date=June 3, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014 | work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref> \n\nThe event has been AAA's annual summer show since 1997, though this marked the first time the event had taken place since 2011. The event featured six matches and was headlined by the AAA in-ring debut of former [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] and [[WWE]] wrestler [[Myzteziz]].\n\n==Production==\n\n===Background===\nFirst held during the summer of 1997 the Mexican [[professional wrestling]], [[wrestling promotion|company]] [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] (AAA, or Triple A) began holding a major wrestling show during the summer, most often in September, called [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]] (\"Summer of Scandal\").<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/mexico/aaa/verano.html | title = Asistencia Asesor\u00eda y Administraci\u00f3n Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo | accessdate = February 19, 2009| publisher= ProWrestlingHistory.com}}</ref> The Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show was an annual event from 1997 until 2011, then AAA did not hold a show in 2012 and 2013 before bringing the show back in 2014, but this time in June, putting it at the time AAA previously held their [[Tripleman\u00eda]]'show. \n\nIn 2012 and 2013 [[Tripleman\u00eda XX]] and [[Tripleman\u00eda XXI]] was held in August instead of the early summer.<ref name=\"Trip20Announced\">{{cite web | url=http://superluchas.net/triplemania-xx-5-de-agosto-en-la-arena-ciudad-de-mexico/ | title= Triplemania XX: 5 de agosto en la Arena Ciudad de M\u00e9xico. | last=Acosta | first=Carlos R. | date= May 31, 2012 | accessdate=June 18, 2012 | work=SuperLuchas | language=Spanish}}</ref> The show often features championship matches or ''[[Lucha de Apuestas]]'' or bet matches where the competitors risked their [[wrestling mask]] or hair on the outcome of the match. In ''[[Lucha Libre]]'' the ''Lucha de Apuetas'' match is considered more prestigious than a championship match and a lot of the major shows feature one or more ''Apuesta'' matches. The 2014 Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show was the 16th show in the series.\n\n===Storylines===\nThe Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show featured six [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] with different wrestlers involved in pre-existing, scripted feuds, plots, and storylines. Wrestlers were portrayed as either [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heels]] (referred to as ''rudos'' in Mexico, those that portray the \"bad guys\") or [[Face (professional wrestling)|faces]] (''t\u00e9cnicos'' in Mexico, the \"good guy\" characters) as they followed a series of tension-building events, which culminated in a wrestling match or series of matches.\n\n==Results==\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://luchalibreaaa.com/resultados/item/1510-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo.html |title=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo |date=June 8, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014 |work=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140702064514/http://luchalibreaaa.com/resultados/item/1510-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo.html |archivedate=July 2, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pwinsider.com/article/86169/the-lucha-report.html?p=1 | title = The Lucha Report | last=Zellner | first=Kris | date=June 9, 2014 | accessdate=June 9, 2014 | work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wrestleview.com/featured-articles/49002-feature-viva-la-raza-lucha-weekly-for-6-14-14 | title = Viva la Raza! Lucha Weekly for 6/14/14 | last=Boutwell | first=Josh | date=June 14, 2014 | accessdate=June 14, 2014 | work=Wrestleview}}</ref>\n|match1=''Los Cadetes del Espacio'' ([[Aero Star]], [[Ludxor]] and [[Venum (wrestler)|Venum]]) defeated [[El Apache]], [[Carta Brava Jr.]] and [[Super Fly (wrestler)|S\u00faper Fly]]\n|stip1=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]]\n|match2=[[El Elegido]], [[Faby Apache]], [[Mascarita Sagrada (2007)|Mascarita Sagrada]] and [[Pimpinela Escarlata]] defeated [[Mamba (wrestler)|Mamba]], [[Mini Abismo Negro]], [[Sexy Star]] and [[Silver King (wrestler)|Silver King]]\n|stip2=Eight-person tag team match\n|match3=[[Ricky Marvin|Bengala]] defeated [[Ang\u00e9lico]], [[Australian Suicide (wrestler)|Australian Suicide]], [[Dark Escoria]], [[F\u00e9nix (wrestler)|F\u00e9nix]], [[El Hijo del Fantasma]], [[Jack Evans (wrestler)|Jack Evans]] and [[Pentag\u00f3n Jr.]]\n|stip3=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|Eight-way elimination match]]; semifinals of a tournament to determine the number one contender to the [[AAA World Cruiserweight Championship|AAA Cruiserweight Championship]]\n|match4=''Los Mexican Power'' ([[Crazy Boy]], [[Joe L\u00edder]] and [[Ni\u00f1o Hamburguesa]]) defeated ''La Anarqu\u00eda'' ([[Daga (wrestler)|Daga]], [[Eterno (wrestler)|Eterno]] and [[Steve Pain]])\n|stip4=Six-man tag team match\n|match5=[[El Texano Jr.]] (c) (with El Hijo del Fantasma) defeated [[Psycho Clown]] (with [[Mini Clown]])\n|stip5=[[Professional wrestling match types#Variations of singles matches|Singles match]] for the [[AAA Mega Championship]]\n|match6=''Ejercito AAA'' ([[Cibern\u00e9tico]], [[Myzteziz]] and [[La Parka II|La Parka]]) defeated ''[[La Sociedad]]'' ([[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Chessman (wrestler)|Chessman]] and [[El Hijo del Perro Aguayo]])\n|stip6=Six-man tag team match\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{AAAPPV|Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo}}\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo'' (2014)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verano De Escandalo 2014}}\n[[Category:2014 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]]\n[[Category:2014 in Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2014 Lucha Libre AAA World Wide event}}\n{{Infobox wrestling event\n|name=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014)\n|image=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014).jpg\n|caption=Promotional poster featuring various [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide|AAA]] wrestlers, including [[Myzteziz]] billed under his old ring name \"M\u00edstico\"\n|tagline=\n|promotion=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]]\n|date=June 7, 2014<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|attendance=7,000<ref>{{cite journal| last = Meltzer | first = Dave | authorlink = Dave Meltzer | date = June 16, 2014 | title = Jun 16 2014 Wrestling Observer Newsletter: Bryan stripped, how it happened, what was known, what happens next, UFC drug test issues and stories behind all of them, Super Juniors, WWE injury updates and contract talks, Rollins direction | journal = [[Dave Meltzer#Wrestling Observer Newsletter|Wrestling Observer Newsletter]] | location = [[Campbell, California]] | issn = 1083-9593 | page=15}}</ref>\n|venue=Plaza de Toros la Concordia<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|city=[[Orizaba]], [[Veracruz]]<ref name=CardAAA/><ref name=CardPWI/>\n|liveevent=Y\n|lastevent=[[Rey de Reyes (2014)|Rey de Reyes]]\n|nextevent=[[Tripleman\u00eda XXII]]\n|event = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2011)|2011]]\n|nextevent2 = [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2015)|2015]]\n}}\n'''Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo (2014)''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for \"Summer of Scandal\") was a [[professional wrestling]] event produced by the [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] (AAA) [[professional wrestling promotion|promotion]], which took place on June 7, 2014, at Plaza de Toros la Concordia in [[Orizaba]], [[Veracruz]], [[Mexico]].<ref name=CardAAA>{{cite web | url = http://luchalibreaaa.com/carteleraaaa/item/1483-junio-7-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo-plaza-de-toros-la-concordia-orizaba-veracruz.html | title = Junio 7 - Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo: Plaza de Toros La Concordia, Orizaba, Veracruz | accessdate=June 8, 2014 | work=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] | language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=CardPWI>{{cite web | url = http://www.pwinsider.com/article/86046/the-lucha-report.html?p=1 | title = The Lucha Report | last=Zellner | first=Kris | date=June 3, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014 | work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref> The event has been AAA's annual summer show since 1997, though this marked the first time the event had taken place since 2011. The event featured six matches and was headlined by the AAA in-ring debut of former [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] and [[WWE]] wrestler [[Myzteziz]].\n\n==Production==\n\n===Background===\nFirst held during the summer of 1997 the Mexican [[professional wrestling]], [[wrestling promotion|company]] [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] (AAA, or Triple A) began holding a major wrestling show during the summer, most often in September, called [[Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]] (\"Summer of Scandal\").<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/mexico/aaa/verano.html | title = Asistencia Asesor\u00eda y Administraci\u00f3n Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo | accessdate = February 19, 2009| publisher= ProWrestlingHistory.com}}</ref> The Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show was an annual event from 1997 until 2011, then AAA did not hold a show in 2012 and 2013 before bringing the show back in 2014, but this time in June, putting it at the time AAA previously held their [[Tripleman\u00eda]]'show. In 2012 and 2013 [[Tripleman\u00eda XX]] and [[Tripleman\u00eda XXI]] was held in August instead of the early summer.<ref name=Trip20Announced>{{cite web | url=http://superluchas.net/triplemania-xx-5-de-agosto-en-la-arena-ciudad-de-mexico/ | title= Triplemania XX: 5 de agosto en la Arena Ciudad de M\u00e9xico. | last=Acosta | first=Carlos R. | date= May 31, 2012 | accessdate=June 18, 2012 | work=SuperLuchas | language=Spanish}}</ref> The show often features championship matches or ''[[Lucha de Apuestas]]'' or bet matches where the competitors risked their [[wrestling mask]] or hair on the outcome of the match. In ''[[Lucha Libre]]'' the ''Lucha de Apuetas'' match is considered more prestigious than a championship match and a lot of the major shows feature one or more ''Apuesta'' matches. The 2014 Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show was the 16th show in the series.\n\n===Storylines===\nThe Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo show featured six [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] with different wrestlers involved in pre-existing, scripted feuds, plots, and storylines. Wrestlers were portrayed as either [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heels]] (referred to as ''rudos'' in Mexico, those that portray the \"bad guys\") or [[Face (professional wrestling)|faces]] (''t\u00e9cnicos'' in Mexico, the \"good guy\" characters) as they followed a series of tension-building events, which culminated in a wrestling match or series of matches.\n\n==Results==\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://luchalibreaaa.com/resultados/item/1510-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo.html |title=Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo |date=June 8, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014 |work=[[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide]] |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140702064514/http://luchalibreaaa.com/resultados/item/1510-verano-de-esc%C3%A1ndalo.html |archivedate=July 2, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pwinsider.com/article/86169/the-lucha-report.html?p=1 | title = The Lucha Report | last=Zellner | first=Kris | date=June 9, 2014 | accessdate=June 9, 2014 | work=Pro Wrestling Insider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wrestleview.com/featured-articles/49002-feature-viva-la-raza-lucha-weekly-for-6-14-14 | title = Viva la Raza! Lucha Weekly for 6/14/14 | last=Boutwell | first=Josh | date=June 14, 2014 | accessdate=June 14, 2014 | work=Wrestleview}}</ref>\n|match1=''Los Cadetes del Espacio'' ([[Aero Star]], [[Ludxor]] and [[Venum (wrestler)|Venum]]) defeated [[El Apache]], [[Carta Brava Jr.]] and [[Super Fly (wrestler)|S\u00faper Fly]]\n|stip1=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]]\n|match2=[[El Elegido]], [[Faby Apache]], [[Mascarita Sagrada (2007)|Mascarita Sagrada]] and [[Pimpinela Escarlata]] defeated [[Mamba (wrestler)|Mamba]], [[Mini Abismo Negro]], [[Sexy Star]] and [[Silver King (wrestler)|Silver King]]\n|stip2=Eight-person tag team match\n|match3=[[Ricky Marvin|Bengala]] defeated [[Ang\u00e9lico]], [[Australian Suicide (wrestler)|Australian Suicide]], [[Dark Escoria]], [[F\u00e9nix (wrestler)|F\u00e9nix]], [[El Hijo del Fantasma]], [[Jack Evans (wrestler)|Jack Evans]] and [[Pentag\u00f3n Jr.]]\n|stip3=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|Eight-way elimination match]]; semifinals of a tournament to determine the number one contender to the [[AAA World Cruiserweight Championship|AAA Cruiserweight Championship]]\n|match4=''Los Mexican Power'' ([[Crazy Boy]], [[Joe L\u00edder]] and [[Ni\u00f1o Hamburguesa]]) defeated ''La Anarqu\u00eda'' ([[Daga (wrestler)|Daga]], [[Eterno (wrestler)|Eterno]] and [[Steve Pain]])\n|stip4=Six-man tag team match\n|match5=[[El Texano Jr.]] (c) (with El Hijo del Fantasma) defeated [[Psycho Clown]] (with [[Mini Clown]])\n|stip5=[[Professional wrestling match types#Variations of singles matches|Singles match]] for the [[AAA Mega Championship]]\n|match6=''Ejercito AAA'' ([[Cibern\u00e9tico]], [[Myzteziz]] and [[La Parka II|La Parka]]) defeated ''[[La Sociedad]]'' ([[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Chessman (wrestler)|Chessman]] and [[El Hijo del Perro Aguayo]])\n|stip6=Six-man tag team match\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{AAAPPV|Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo}}\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo'' (2014)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verano De Escandalo 2014}}\n[[Category:2014 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:Verano de Esc\u00e1ndalo]]\n[[Category:2014 in Mexico]]\n", "name_user": "Infoga