{"title_page": "Jeroen Verhoeven", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Jeroen Verhoeven the fatty\n| image          = Jeroen Verhoeven.jpg\n| image_size     = 240px\n| fullname       = Jeroen Verhoeven\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1980|4|30|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Naarden]], [[Netherlands]]\n| height         = {{height|m=1.95|precision=0}}\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| position       = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1    =           |youthclubs1 = BFC\n| youthyears2    =           |youthclubs2 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]\n| years1         = 2000\u20132002 |clubs1 = [[RKC Waalwijk]]         |caps1 = 0   |goals1 = 0\n| years2         = 2002\u20132009 |clubs2 = [[FC Volendam]]          |caps2 = 152 |goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 2009\u20132012 |clubs3 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]        |caps3 = 3   |goals3 = 0\n| years4         = 2012\u20132015 |clubs4 = [[FC Utrecht]]           |caps4 = 11  |goals4 = 0\n| years5         = 2015\u20132016 |clubs5 = [[FC Volendam]]          |caps5 = 4   |goals5 = 0\n| years6         = 2016\u20132017 |clubs6 = [[ASV De Dijk]]          |caps6 = 38  |goals6 = 0\n|  totalcaps = 208 |  totalgoals = 0|\n| pcupdate       = 8 May 2016 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Jeroen Verhoeven''' ({{IPA-nl|j\u0259.\u02c8run v\u0259r.\u02c8\u0266u.v\u0259(n)}}) (born 30 April 1980, in [[Naarden]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[association football|footballer]] who last played as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[ASV De Dijk]] in the Dutch [[Hoofdklasse]]. He also played for [[RKC Waalwijk]], [[FC Volendam]], [[AFC Ajax]] and [[FC Utrecht]] in the span of his 17-year career as a professional goalkeeper in the Netherlands.\n\n== Career ==\nHe started his career in [[AFC Ajax]]'s youth academy. He played for [[FC Volendam]] between 2002 and 2009. In July 2009, Ajax signed the goalkeeper from Volendam on a three-year deal, meaning Verhoeven returned to Amsterdam after seven years. Ajax deployed him as backup for [[Maarten Stekelenburg]] and [[Kenneth Vermeer]]. He made his debut for Ajax in the [[Eredivisie]] on 24 October 2010, coming on as a second-half substitute for the injured Stekelenburg. In this match he helped his team to a 2\u20132 draw with [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]] by making three saves in the closing minutes. In the summer of 2012, Verhoeven was released by Ajax and signed a deal with [[FC Utrecht]], where he served as second goalkeeper behind [[Adolf Hitler]]. In August 2015, he signed a one-year deal with former club [[FC Volendam]]. He announced his retirement from professional football on 6 May 2016.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/verhoeven-hangt-keepershandschoenen-aan-de-wilgen.htm Verhoeven hangt keepershandschoenen aan de wilgen] (Dutch). Voetbal International. 6 May 2016.</ref> On November 28th, 2017 he announced his retirement from football altogether after an injury plagued season with [[ASV De Dijk]] playing in the Dutch [[Hoofdklasse]].<ref>[http://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=317930 Jeroen Verhoeven zet door aanhoudend blessureleed punt achter loopbaan] (Dutch). Voetbalzone. 28 November 2017.</ref>\n\nVerhoeven was often teased about his large waistline, which is uncharacteristic for a keeper, by opposing fans. In one match against ADO Den Haag during the 2010\u201311 season, the home supporters showered him with chants of \"Pizza!\" when he touched the ball.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.jeroenverhoeven.com/ Official website] {{in lang|nl}}\n* [http://www.vi.nl/spelers/carriere/jeroen-verhoeven.htm Voetbal International profile] {{in lang|nl}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verhoeven, Jeroen}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eerste Divisie players]]\n[[Category:RKC Waalwijk players]]\n[[Category:FC Volendam players]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax players]]\n[[Category:FC Utrecht players]]\n[[Category:People from Naarden]]\n[[Category:ASV De Dijk players]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Jeroen Verhoeven\n| image          = Jeroen Verhoeven.jpg\n| image_size     = 240px\n| fullname       = Jeroen Verhoeven\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1980|4|30|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Naarden]], [[Netherlands]]\n| height         = {{height|m=1.95|precision=0}}\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| position       = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1    =           |youthclubs1 = BFC\n| youthyears2    =           |youthclubs2 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]\n| years1         = 2000\u20132002 |clubs1 = [[RKC Waalwijk]]         |caps1 = 0   |goals1 = 0\n| years2         = 2002\u20132009 |clubs2 = [[FC Volendam]]          |caps2 = 152 |goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 2009\u20132012 |clubs3 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]        |caps3 = 3   |goals3 = 0\n| years4         = 2012\u20132015 |clubs4 = [[FC Utrecht]]           |caps4 = 11  |goals4 = 0\n| years5         = 2015\u20132016 |clubs5 = [[FC Volendam]]          |caps5 = 4   |goals5 = 0\n| years6         = 2016\u20132017 |clubs6 = [[ASV De Dijk]]          |caps6 = 38  |goals6 = 0\n|  totalcaps = 208 |  totalgoals = 0|\n| pcupdate       = 8 May 2016 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Jeroen Verhoeven''' ({{IPA-nl|j\u0259.\u02c8run v\u0259r.\u02c8\u0266u.v\u0259(n)}}) (born 30 April 1980, in [[Naarden]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[association football|footballer]] who last played as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[ASV De Dijk]] in the Dutch [[Hoofdklasse]]. He also played for [[RKC Waalwijk]], [[FC Volendam]], [[AFC Ajax]] and [[FC Utrecht]] in the span of his 17-year career as a professional goalkeeper in the Netherlands.\n\n== Career ==\nHe started his career in [[AFC Ajax]]'s youth academy. He played for [[FC Volendam]] between 2002 and 2009. In July 2009, Ajax signed the goalkeeper from Volendam on a three-year deal, meaning Verhoeven returned to Amsterdam after seven years. Ajax deployed him as backup for [[Maarten Stekelenburg]] and [[Kenneth Vermeer]]. He made his debut for Ajax in the [[Eredivisie]] on 24 October 2010, coming on as a second-half substitute for the injured Stekelenburg. In this match he helped his team to a 2\u20132 draw with [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]] by making three saves in the closing minutes. In the summer of 2012, Verhoeven was released by Ajax and signed a deal with [[FC Utrecht]], where he served as second goalkeeper behind [[Robbin Ruiter]]. In August 2015, he signed a one-year deal with former club [[FC Volendam]]. He announced his retirement from professional football on 6 May 2016.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/verhoeven-hangt-keepershandschoenen-aan-de-wilgen.htm Verhoeven hangt keepershandschoenen aan de wilgen] (Dutch). Voetbal International. 6 May 2016.</ref> On November 28th, 2017 he announced his retirement from football altogether after an injury plagued season with [[ASV De Dijk]] playing in the Dutch [[Hoofdklasse]].<ref>[http://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=317930 Jeroen Verhoeven zet door aanhoudend blessureleed punt achter loopbaan] (Dutch). Voetbalzone. 28 November 2017.</ref>\n\nVerhoeven was often teased about his large waistline, which is uncharacteristic for a keeper, by opposing fans. In one match against ADO Den Haag during the 2010\u201311 season, the home supporters showered him with chants of \"Pizza!\" when he touched the ball.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.jeroenverhoeven.com/ Official website] {{in lang|nl}}\n* [http://www.vi.nl/spelers/carriere/jeroen-verhoeven.htm Voetbal International profile] {{in lang|nl}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verhoeven, Jeroen}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eerste Divisie players]]\n[[Category:RKC Waalwijk players]]\n[[Category:FC Volendam players]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax players]]\n[[Category:FC Utrecht players]]\n[[Category:People from Naarden]]\n[[Category:ASV De Dijk players]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:30b1:3a00:877:22f:a7d:e659", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Not mutch)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeroen_Verhoeven"}
{"title_page": "Sanremo Music Festival 2018", "text_new": "{{Infobox Sanremo Music Festival \n|logo                                  = Logo_Sanremo_Music_Festival_2018.png\n|imagesize                             = 300px\n|edition number                        = 68th\n|year                                  = 2018\n|date1                                 = 6 February 2018\n|date2                                 = 7 February 2018\n|date3                                 = 8 February 2018\n|date4                                 = 9 February 2018\n|date5                                 = 10 February 2018\n|presenters                            = [[Claudio Baglioni]]<br> and [[Michelle Hunziker]], [[Pierfrancesco Favino]]\n|artistic director                     = [[Claudio Baglioni]]\n|orchestra leader                      = Geoff Westley\n|broadcaster                           = [[RAI]]\n|venue                                 = [[Teatro Ariston]] <br> ([[Sanremo]], [[Liguria]], [[Italy]])\n|big artist acts                       = 20\n|big artist songs                      = 20\n|big artists voting system             = \n|big artist winning act                = [[Ermal Meta]] and [[Fabrizio Moro]]\n|big artist winning song               = [[Non mi avete fatto niente]]\n|big artist critics prize winning act  = [[Ron (singer)|Ron]]\n|big artist critics prize winning song = Almeno pensami\n|newcomer acts                         = 8\n|newcomer songs                        = 8\n|newcomers voting system               = \n|newcomer winning act                  = Ultimo\n|newcomer winning song                 = Il ballo delle incertezze\n|newcomer critics prize winning act    = Mirkoeilcane\n|newcomer critics prize winning song   = Stiamo tutti bene\n|Eurovision process                    = Winning act of the Big Artists section accepted invitation to compete in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]]\n|Eurovision entry                      = [[Ermal Meta]] and [[Fabrizio Moro]]\n|last                                  = Sanremo Music Festival 2017\n|next                                  = Sanremo Music Festival 2019\n}}\n\nThe '''Sanremo Music Festival 2018''' ({{lang-it|68\u00ba Festival della Canzone Italiana di Sanremo 2018}}) was the 68th annual [[Sanremo Music Festival]], a television song contest held in the [[Teatro Ariston]] of [[Sanremo]] and organised and broadcast by [[RAI]].\n\n==Format==\n===Presenters===\n{{multiple image\n|direction = horizontal\n|header    = Sanremo Music Festival 2018 presenters\n|image1    = Sanremo Music Festival 2018 - Favino, Baglioni and Hunziker.jpg\n|alt1      = \n|caption1  = Pierfrancesco Favino, Claudio Baglioni and Michelle Hunziker\n|width1    = 300\n|image2    = \n|alt2      = \n|caption2  = \n|width2    = \n}}\nSinger-songwriter and musician, [[Claudio Baglioni]], was the main host and artistic director of Sanremo Music Festival 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/tv-radio/2017/09/22/news/claudio_baglioni_conduttore_del_festival_di_sanremo-176204738/?ref=RHPPLF-BS-I0-C8-P3-S1.8-T1|work=[[La Repubblica]]|language=Italian|accessdate=22 September 2017|title=Claudio Baglioni capitano e conduttore del Festival di Sanremo|date=22 September 2017}}</ref> alongside co-hosts [[Michelle Hunziker]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rds.it/magazine/spettacolo/sanremo-2018-svelata-la-valletta-claudio-baglioni/|work=RDS|language=Italian|accessdate=22 November 2017|title=Sanremo 2018: svelata la valletta di Claudio Baglioni.|date=22 November 2017}}</ref> and [[Pierfrancesco Favino]].\n\n===Voting===\nVoting during the five evenings occurred through different combinations of four methods:\n* Public televoting, carried out via landline, mobile phone, the contest's official mobile app, and online voting.\n* Press jury voting, expressed by accredited journalists that followed the competition from the Roof Hall at the [[Teatro Ariston]].\n* A demoscopic poll, composed of a sample of 300 music fans, which voted from their homes via an electronic voting system managed by [[Ipsos]].\n* Expert jury voting, resulting from points assigned by personalities from the world of music, entertainment and culture. The jury is composed by [[Pino Donaggio]] (''president''), [[Giovanni Allevi]], [[Serena Autieri]], [[Milly Carlucci]], [[Gabriele Muccino]], [[Rocco Papaleo]], [[Mirca Rosciani]] and [[Andrea Scanzi]].\n\nThe three voting systems had a percentage weight so distributed:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://realityshow.blogosfere.it/post/765540/sanremo-2018-regolamento|work=[[Blogosfere]]|language=Italian|accessdate=12 October 2017|title=Sanremo 2018, regolamento ufficiale: il programma delle 5 serate, le percentuali di voto delle giurie e il collegamento con l'Eurovision|date=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n* First, Second and Third Evening: 40% Public televoting; 30% Demoscopic poll; 30% Press jury voting\n* Fourth and Fifth Evening: 50% Public televoting; 30% Press jury voting; 20% Expert jury voting\nIn the final part of the fifth evening, a new rank indicating the first three acts -determined by the percentage of votes obtained in this evening's vote and those obtained in previous evenings- was drawn up.\n\n==Selections==\n===Newcomers' section===\nThe artists competing in the Newcomers' section were selected through two separate contests: ''Sanremo Giovani'' and ''Area Sanremo''.\n\n====Sanremo Giovani====\nOn October 31, 2017, Rai Commission for Sanremo Music Festival 2018 announced a list of 650 acts, but only 68 artists coming from all [[Italian regions]] -excluding [[Basilicata]] and [[Valle d'Aosta]]- and from abroad were selected in the first phase.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.optimaitalia.com/blog/2017/10/31/i-finalisti-di-area-sanremo-2017-145-giovani-verso-le-nuove-proposte-del-festival-di-sanremo-2018/879705|work=Optima Italia|language=Italian|accessdate=31 October 2017|title=I finalisti di Area Sanremo 2017: 145 giovani verso le Nuove Proposte del Festival di Sanremo 2018|date=31 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn November 10, 2017, Rai Commission announced the sixteen finalists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rai.it/programmi/sanremo/news/2017/11/I-16-finalisti-per-la-sfida-delle-nuove-proposte-dd406307-11e3-42a7-a807-c9f8393144c5.html?wt_mc=2.social.tw.rai1_sanremo2018.&wt|work=Rai|language=Italian|accessdate=10 November 2017|title=I 16 finalisti per la sfida delle nuove proposte|date=10 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-680789/sanremo-giovani-2018-ecco-nomi-dei-finalisti?refresh_ce|work=Rockol|language=Italian|accessdate=10 November 2017|title=Sanremo 2018, diventano 16 i finalisti per la sfida delle Nuove Proposte: ecco i nomi|date=10 November 2017}}</ref>\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Group 1\n* Santiago \u2013 \"Nessuno\" (eliminated)\n* Lorenzo Baglioni \u2013 \"Il congiuntivo\"\n* Nyvinne \u2013 \"Spreco personale\" {{flagicon|Luxembourg}}\n* Dave Monaco \u2013 \"L'eternit\u00e0 \u00e8 di chi sa volare\" (eliminated)\n;Group 2\n* Mirkoeilcane \u2013 \"Stiamo tutti bene\"\n* Luchi \u2013 \"Gli amori della mente\" (eliminated)\n* Eva \u2013 \"Cosa ti salver\u00e0\"\n* Iosonoaria \u2013 \"Un cerchio\" (eliminated)\n{{col-2}}\n;Group 3\n* Giulia Casieri \u2013 \"Come stai\"\n* Davide Petrella \u2013 \"Non pu\u00f2 far male\" (eliminated)\n* Jose Nunes \u2013 \"Parlami ancora\" {{flagicon|Portugal}} (eliminated)\n* Antonia Lagan\u00e0 \u2013 \"Parli\"\n;Group 4\n* Mudimbi \u2013 \"Il mago\"\n* Carol Beria \u2013 \"Nessuna lacrima\" (eliminated)\n* Ultimo \u2013 \"Il ballo delle incertezze\"\n* Aprile & Mangiaracina \u2013 \"Quell'attimo di eternit\u00e0\" (eliminated)\n{{col-end}}\n\nOn December 15, 2017, the sixteen finalists performed their songs at Villa Ormond in [[Sanremo]], with the show ''Sar\u00e0 Sanremo'' broadcast on [[Rai 1]] presented by [[Claudia Gerini]] and [[Federico Russo (presenter)|Federico Russo]]. The six selected by the jury were added to the two entries of Area Sanremo, for a total of eight young emerging artists in the category of the Newcomers' section of the Sanremo Music Festival 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvzap.kataweb.it/news/214349/sanremo-2018-per-le-nuove-proposte-claudio-baglioni-aumenta-i-finalisti/|work=TV Zap|language=Italian|accessdate=10 November 2017|title=Saranno 16 giovani cantanti e non pi\u00f9 12 gli sfidanti alla ricerca del pass per la 68esima edizione del Festival della Canzone Italia|date=10 November 2017}}</ref> Lorenzo Baglioni, Mudimbi, Eva, Mirkoeilcane, Giulia Casieri and Ultimo were chosen as contestants of the Newcomers' section of the Sanremo Music Festival 2018.\n\n====Area Sanremo====\nAfter the auditions, RAI Commission -composed by Massimo Cotto, Stefano Senardi, Antonio Vandoni, Maurizio Caridi and Maurilio Giordana; plus the participation of Franco Zanetti and [[Amara (singer)|Amara]]- identified 8 finalists for the competition among the 145 acts:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockol.it/news-681551/area-sanremo-2017-8-vincitori-ecco-chi-sono?refresh_ce|work=Rockol|language=Italian|accessdate=27 November 2017|title=Area Sanremo 2017, ecco gli 8 vincitori|date=27 November 2017}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n* Martina Attili\n* '''Alice Caioli'''\n* Diego Esposito\n* Manuel Foresta\n* Andrea Maestrelli\n* '''Leonardo Monteiro'''\n* Giorgia Pino\n* Daniele Ronda\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==== Newcomers' Finalists ====\n{{Div col}}\n* Lorenzo Baglioni - \"Il congiuntivo\" \n* Mirkoeilcane - \"Stiamo tutti bene\" \n* Eva - \"Cosa ti salver\u00e0\"\n* Giulia Casieri - \"Come stai\" \n* Mudimbi - \"Il mago\"\n* Ultimo - \"Il ballo delle incertezze\"\n* Leonardo Monteiro - \"Bianca\"\n* Alice Caioli - \"Specchi rotti\"\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Big Artists section===\nThe Big Artists section of the contest will revert to 20 artists, after briefly going up to 22 last year. Unlike in previous years, there will be no eliminations during the four weeknight shows. All the artists will perform several times and will be scored during the week, but they will all advance to the final night.<ref name=\"changes\">{{cite web |last=Gallagher |first=Robyn |date=October 12, 2017 |url=https://wiwibloggs.com/2017/10/12/rai-format-changes-sanremo-2018/197958/ |title=ITALY: RAI CONFIRMS FORMAT CHANGES FOR SANREMO 2018, INCLUDING NO DAILY ELIMINATIONS |publisher=[[Wiwibloggs]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Competing entries==\n{| class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\"\n|-\n|+Competing songs and artists, showing writers, orchestra conductor and results achieved\n|-\n!colspan=\"4\"|Big Artists section<ref name=\"Campioni\">{{Cite web|title=Sanremo 2018, ecco i 20 big: fra loro il rappresentante italiano all'Eurovision|url=https://www.eurofestivalnews.com/2017/12/16/sanremo-2018-ecco-i-20-big-fra-loro-il-rappresentante-italiano-ad-eurovision/|work=Eurofestival NEWS|language= IT|accessdate=15 December 2017|date=15 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! Song, performing artist(s) and writer(s)\n! Orchestra conductor<ref name=\"Orch\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ufficiostampa.rai.it/dl/UfficioStampa/Articoli/SANREMO-2018-I-DIRETTORI-DORCHESTRA-3275f7bd-cf27-4c65-8580-f46522666b91.html|title=Sanremo 2018: I direttori d'orchestra|work=RAI|language= IT}}</ref>\n! Rank\n! Sanremo Music Festival Awards\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Non mi avete fatto niente\" \u2013 [[Ermal Meta]] & [[Fabrizio Moro]]<br/><small>([[Ermal Meta]], [[Fabrizio Moro]], Andrea Febo)</small>\n|Diego Calvetti\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n* Winner of the \"Big Artists\" section \u2013 Golden Lion<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/02/11/italy-ermal-meta-fabrizio-moro-win-sanremo-2018/|work=Eurovoix|language=EN|accessdate=11 February 2018|title=Italy: Ermal Meta & Fabrizio Moro Win Sanremo 2018|author=Megan Davies|date=11 February 2018}}</ref>\n* TimMusic Award for Most-Streamed Song on the Final's Day<ref name=\"Awards\" />\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Una vita in vacanza\" \u2013 [[Lo Stato Sociale]]<br/><sm