did not happen in this edition. In the event that the winner decides not to compete in the Eurovision Song Contest, [[RAI]] and the organisers of [[Sanremo Music Festival]] usually reserve the right to select the Italian entrant to themselves, in the case of 2016 selecting runner-up [[Francesca Michielin]]. \n\nThere were several former Italian Eurovision representatives feature in the Big Artists category this year. [[Nina Zilli]] came 9th in 2012 with \"[[L'amore \u00e8 femmina (song)|L'amore \u00e8 femmina (Out of love)]]\". [[Riccardo Fogli]] came 11th in 1983 with \"Per Lucia\". [[Enrico Ruggeri]], the lead singer of [[Decibel (group)|Decibel]], came 12th in 1993 with \"Sole d'Europa\" and [[Luca Barbarossa]] also came 12th in 1988 with \"Vivo (Ti scrivo)\".\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Sanremo Music Festival}}\n[[Category:2018 in Italian television]]\n[[Category:2018 song contests]]\n[[Category:February 2018 events in Italy]]\n[[Category:Sanremo Music Festival by year]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toFederico Russo(link changed toFederico Russo (presenter)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanremo_Music_Festival_2018"}
{"title_page": "Blue (Da Ba Dee)", "text_new": "{{short description|1998 single by Eiffel 65}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Blue (If I was green I would die)\n| cover      = Eiffel65BlueDaBaDeeCDSingleCover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Eiffel 65]] \n| album      = [[Europop (album)|Europop]]\n| B-side     = Remix\n| released   = October 7, 1998<ref name=\"billb\"/>\n| format     =\n*[[CD single|CD]]\n*[[maxi single|maxi CD]]\n| recorded   = September 1998\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Eurodance]]<ref>{{cite news |url= http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/E/Eiffel_65/2000/03/25/pf-744854.html |title= Forgotten song became hit for Eiffel 65 |work= [[Canoe.ca]] |date= 25 March 2000 |first= Lisa |last= Wilton |accessdate= 12 May 2014 |archive-url= https://archive.is/20140330020626/http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/E/Eiffel_65/2000/03/25/pf-744854.html |archive-date= 2014-03-30 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n| length     =\n*4:45 (album version)\n*3:39 (video edit)\n*3:29 (US radio edit)\n| label      = Bliss Corporation\n| writer     =\n*[[Jeffrey Jey]]\n*[[Maurizio Lobina]]\n*Massimo Gabutti\n| producer   =\n*Maurizio Lobina\n*Gabry Ponte\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Too Much of Heaven]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\"'''Blue (Da Ba Dee)'''\" is a song by Italian music group [[Eiffel 65]]. It was first released in October 7, 1998 in [[Italy]] by Bliss Corporation and became internationally successful the following year.<ref name=\"billb\">[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=sA0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA114&lpg=PA114&dq=blue+da+ba+dee+october+1998&source=bl&ots=64AP9f_fi1&sig=9DmdMl-OQ_-JF8jI6UhSGmLlK44&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjrwsv40ovaAhUILpQKHdrsC_AQ6AEIVTAG#v=onepage&q=blue%20da%20ba%20dee%20october%201998&f=false] \"Billboard Magazine\"</ref> It is the lead single of their debut album ''[[Europop (album)|Europop]]''. The song is the group's most popular single, reaching number one in many countries such as [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], the [[United Kingdom]],<ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\">{{cite book| first= David| last= Roberts| year= 2006| title= [[British Hit Singles & Albums]]| edition= 19th| publisher= Guinness World Records Limited| location= London| isbn= 1-904994-10-5| page= 638}}</ref> the [[Netherlands]], [[France]], [[Sweden]], [[Switzerland]], [[Spain]], [[Portugal]], [[Canada]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[Russia]], [[New Zealand]], [[Israel]], [[Lebanon]], [[Finland]], [[Norway]], [[Belgium]], [[Australia]], [[Austria]], [[Greece]], [[Germany]], and [[Hungary]], as well as reaching #6 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in the [[United States]] in January 2000.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=eiffel 65|chart=all}} Billboard.com - Artist Chart History - Eiffel 65<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nIn the United Kingdom, the song originally entered the top 40 purely on import sales; it was only the third single to do this.<ref name=\"songfacts\">{{cite web| url= http://www.songfacts.com/detail.php?id=2905| title = Blue (Da Ba Dee)| work = Songfacts.com| accessdate = 2009-03-31}}</ref> The song also received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording|Best Dance Recording]] at the [[2001 Grammy Awards]], two years after it was released.<ref>http://www.rockonthenet.com/archive/2001/grammys.htm</ref>\n\n==Writing and production==\n\"Blue\", written by Eiffel 65 lead singer [[Jeffrey Jey]], keyboardist [[Maurizio Lobina]], and producer Massimo Gabutti, it was known for Underground Warriors, was inspired by group member Maurizio Lobina's composed opening piano [[Hook (music)|hook]]. The producers of the song then came up with the idea for a dance song. Jey stated that his inspiration for the lyrics was how a person picked his lifestyle. The colour blue as the main topic of the song was picked at random, with Lobina telling him to write nonsensical lyrics. Gabutti came up with the \"da ba dee\" hook.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=epnsRRPtoeU</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ross |first1=Mike |title=The Colour of Money Is Blue |url=http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/E/Eiffel_65/2000/03/25/744855.html |website=[[Jam!]] |publisher=Canoe Inc. |accessdate=23 April 2009 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120525125353/http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/Artists/E/Eiffel_65/2000/03/25/744855.html# |archivedate=2012-05-25 |df= }}</ref> The pitch-shifted vocal effect used in the song was created with a [[harmonizer]].<ref>{{cite AV media|author1=Coburn, Dylan (Director, Producer)|author2=Boccardi, Silva (Producer)|date=21 March 2019|title=The Story of \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" by Eiffel 65|type=YouTube video|language=English|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=epnsRRPtoeU&t=10m14s|access-date=19 May 2019|publisher=[[VICE Media]]|series=''The Story Of''}}</ref>\n\n==Lyrics and composition==\n{{Listen|filename = Blue (Da Ba Dee) sample.ogg|title = Eiffel 65 \u2013 \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\", 1999|description = A 29-second sample of Jeffrey Jey's vocals on \"Blue (Da Ba Dee).\" The song was one of the first ever popular tracks to use pitch correction.|format = [[Ogg]]\n}}\n\"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" is written in the key of [[G minor]], with the vocal range spanning from C<sub>3</sub> to E{{flat}}<sub>4</sub>,<ref>[http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0034964& Eiffel 65 - Blue (Da Ba Dee) Sheet Music (Download and Print)]. Musicnotes.com. Accessed from April 28, 2013.</ref> and is set in [[common time]] with a moderate tempo of 128 beats per minute.<ref>[http://people.cs.ubc.ca/~davet/music/artist/E/E4.html Dave's Music Database - Eiffel 65]</ref>\n\nThe song's lyrics tell a story about a man who lives in a \"[[blue]] world.\" It is also stated he is \"blue inside and outside,\" which, along with the lyric \"himself and everybody around 'cause he ain't got nobody to listen,\" and \"blue are the feelings that live inside me\" may indicate that the term ''blue'' represents his emotional state; however, the song also states that a vast variety of what he owns is also blue, including his house and his car (\"a blue Corvette\"): various blue-coloured objects are also depicted on the single's cover.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120721170411/http://prod-assets.mog.com/amg/pop/cov200/dre000/e030/e030542oof9.jpg prod-assets.mog.com - Eiffel 65 \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" single cover]</ref> The song's hook is the sentence \"I'm blue,\" followed by a repetition of the sounds \"da ba dee da ba daa\", which the hook is based around. This sound shared by related compositions such as \"[[Around the World (La La La La La)]]\" by [[A Touch of Class (band)|ATC]] that surfaced around the same time.<ref>[https://www.complex.com/music/2013/07/10-essential-eurodance-classics/]</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received mixed reviews from critics. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' wrote that \"the hook here, with its dancy but curiously compelling singsongy rhythm and lyric, is destined to react instantly with listeners far and wide.\" They also noted that it has a \"euro sound\" and \"it's creative, it will affect listeners on both ends of the demographic spectrum, and it's anthemic.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/90s/1999/BB-1999-11-27.pdf|title=Single Review: New & Noteworthy|work=Billboard magazine|date=November 27, 1999|accessdate=February 10, 2020|page=27|format=PDF}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' positively reviewed the song, calling the song \"a fleeting, feel-good foot-tapper\" and gave the song a rating of B-.<ref>[http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,275134,00.html Blue (Da Ba Dee) | Music Review |Entertainment Weekly]</ref> The Daily Vault's Christopher Thelen described it as a \"quirky little hit\" with a \"bouncy chorus\". He also noted that \"the key is the use of the voice synthesizer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyvault.com/toc.php5?review=1020|title=Eiffel 65 - Europop|website=The Daily Vault|date=February 27, 2000|accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref> ''[[PopMatters]]'' reviewer Chris Massey, in his review of ''Europop'', described his initial reaction to the song as being \"really, really bad.\" However, he later stated in the review that after many repeated listenings of the song he \"loved it.\"<ref>[http://www.popmatters.com/music/reviews/e/eiffel65-europop.shtml Eiffel 65: Europop - PopMatters Music Review]</ref> [[AllMusic]] editor Jose F. Promis described the song as a \"hypnotic smash\" in his review of ''Europop''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/europop-mw0000257752|title=Eiffel 65 - Europop|work=AllMusic|date=|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'', however, in their review of ''Europop'', gave the song a negative review, stating that the song \"blends [[Cher]]-esque [[vocoder]] vocals, trance-like synth riffs, unabashed Eurodisco beats and a baby-babble chorus so infantile it makes the [[Teletubbies]] sound like [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]].\" The magazine also placed the song on their list of the \"20 Most Annoying Songs,\" at No. 14.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110501051217/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/blogs/staff-blog/the-20-most-annoying-songs-20070702 20 Most Annoying Songs by ''Rolling Stone''].</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nThe single, released in October 1998, was a [[chart-topper]] in many European countries. The song initially found success in France, where it debuted in August 1999 and reached number one for three weeks. It then found success in other European countries, reaching the top spot on many charts in September the same year, including Germany, the Netherlands,<ref>[http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Eiffel+65&titel=Blue+%28Da+Ba+Dee%29&cat=s Dutchcharts.nl - 65 - Blue (Da Ba Dee)]   {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306114421/http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Eiffel+65&titel=Blue+%28Da+Ba+Dee%29&cat=s |date=March 6, 2014  }}</ref> Switzerland,<ref>[http://hitparade.ch/showitem.asp?interpret=Eiffel+65&titel=Blue+%28Da+Ba+Dee%29&cat=s Hitparade.ch - Eiffel 65 - Blue (Da Ba Dee)]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091103224424/http://hitparade.ch/showitem.asp?interpret=Eiffel%2065&titel=Blue%20%28Da%20Ba%20Dee%29&cat=s |date=November 3, 2009 }}</ref> Sweden,<ref>[http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Eiffel+65&titel=Blue+%28Da+Ba+Dee%29&cat=s Swedishcharts.com - Eiffel 65 - Blue (Da Ba Dee)]</ref> Norway and many other countries. It replaced \"[[Mambo No. 5]]\" by [[Lou Bega]] on many of these charts at the top spot. In the [[United Kingdom]], the song spent three weeks at the top of the singles chart in September and October, eventually becoming the second biggest selling single of that year in the country behind \"[[Baby One More Time (single)|Baby One More Time]]\" by [[Britney Spears]].\n\nThe song also found success in other regions, including Oceania and North America: it reached number one in Australia, New Zealand and Canada. It became a top ten hit on the U.S. ''Billboard'' Hot 100, reaching number six. It became the highest charting Italian song in the United States since [[Al di l\u00e0]] by [[Emilio Pericoli]] that also peaked at six in 1962.\n\nThe song re-charted on 6 May 2013 at No. 40 in the [[United Kingdom|U.K.]],<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/chart/dancesingles BBC Radio 1 Charts]. [[BBC]]. 6 May 2013. Accessed from 6 May 2013.</ref> the same week the song appeared in the film ''[[Iron Man 3]]''.\n\n==Music video==\n[[File:Eiffel 65 Blue video.jpg|thumb|200px|Eiffel 65 on television screens during the opening segment of the video.]]\nThe music video for the song was released in 1999 by BlissCoMedia, a computer graphics division of Bliss Corporation, known at the time the video was produced and released as BlissMultiMedia.<ref name = \"Blisscomedia10\">[http://www.blisscomedia.com/ Blue: 10 anni, 10 milioni di download] (In Italian). Blisscomedia.com. Accessed from May 11, 2013.</ref>\n\nLike much of the Bliss Corporation's music videos, this one was done in a [[green screen]] garage studio at BlissCoMedia,<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130305232749/http://www.eiffel65.com/index.php/eiffel65/comments/iltedesco_eiffel65s_forum_mod_made_an_interview_with_davide_la_sala_former_/|title=Eiffel 65 Planet - IlTedesco, Eiffel65\u2019s forum Mod made an interview with Davide La Sala,\u00a0 former BlissCo Media employe|date=2013-03-05|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blisscomedia.com/blisscomedia_v3/studio.php|title=BLISSCOMEDIA|website=www.blisscomedia.com|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref> and it featured computer-generated graphics that were done in [[Autodesk 3ds Max|3ds Max]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blisscomedia.com/blisscomedia_v3/renderfarm.php|title=BLISSCOMEDIA|website=www.blisscomedia.com|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref> With very few resources, tutorials and books, and only one editing machine, the video was made between 1998 and 1999 in a garage in about 2 to 3 months, much like other videos made by BlissCo.<sup>[[Blue (Da Ba Dee) (music video)#cite%20note-Davide%20La%20Sala-6|[6]]]</sup>\n\nFormer BlissCo employee Davide La Sala has stated about coming up with the story for the video: \"We had brainstorming sessions and we were a very imaginative team, huge fans of sci-fi movies and video games: ''[[Blade Runner]]'', ''[[Star Wars]]'', etc\u2026 we were master in doing our best and working with the few tools we had to create complete short stories in a very short period of time.\"<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nSimilar to other music videos by BlissCo, a total of five people worked on this video. The green-screen footage was done in a short amount of time, and some of it was put into a computer generated 3D environment, while components of the band were also shot. La Sala said, \"We were very flexible but every person in the team had his own special skill who was more towards motion graphics, design and editing, others more skilled in architectural design and me and the CEO experts in animation.\"<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nThe video was listed in [[NME]]'s \"50 Worst Music Videos Ever\".<ref>{{cite web |title=50 Worst Music Videos Ever |url=http://www.nme.com/list/50-worst-music-videos-ever/253198/page/2 |website=[[NME]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111203205813/http://www.nme.com/list/50-worst-music-videos-ever/253198/page/2 |archivedate=December 3, 2011}}</ref>\n\n=== Synopsis ===\nThe video takes place on Tukon4, where lead singer [[Jeffrey Jey]] is abducted by blue [[Extraterrestrial life|aliens]] Zorotl and Sayok6 during a concert.<ref name=\":0\">[http://www.zorotl.com/zorotl_story7.php Jeffrey-kidnapped]</ref> The aliens then proceed to leave [[Earth]] with him. Group members [[Maurizio Lobina]] and [[Gabry Ponte]] chase after them in their own small [[spacecraft]], and eventually both ships arrive on the blue aliens' [[planet]] via a portal.\n\nIt is then shown that Jey was abducted to perform in a concert for the aliens, with him singing the same song he was about to sing when he was taken. He slowly realises that the crowd is composed entirely of strange blue beings, which are known as Tukonians,<ref name=\":0\" /> and becomes increasingly concerned.\n\nAfter fighting off a number of alien guards using [[martial arts]] and several energy-based, psionic abilities, including force lightning, Lobina and Ponte succeed in rescuing Jey. While leaving the planet, they are asked to return by the aliens. They oblige, and spend the remaining duration of the video performing a concert for the blue-skinned extraterrestrials with Zorotl joining them on stage, creating a friendship between the band and the creatures. These events possibly lead into the scenario in the music video for \"[[Move Your Body (Eiffel 65 song)|Move Your Body]]\".\n\nThe events in the video share no relation to the song's lyrical content apart from the fact that the aliens all have blue skin.\n\n==Cover versions and samplings==\nGerman singer [[Max Raabe]] and Palast Orchester covered the song for his 2001 studio album ''Super Hits''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palastorchester.de/index.php?id=13 |title=Max Raabe und Palast Orchester News, Bilder, Konzerte und Videos 2011 - Home |publisher=Palastorchester.de |date= |accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref> A cover version was released on the 2006 [[Crazy Frog]] studio album ''[[Crazy Frog Presents More Crazy Hits|More Crazy Hits]]''. [[Flo Rida]] sampled the chorus of \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" in his 2009 single \"[[Sugar (Flo Rida song)|Sugar]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://top40.about.com/b/2009/03/09/flo-rida-digs-out-eiffel-65s-blue-da-ba-dee-for-new-single-sugar.htm |title=Flo Rida Digs Out Eiffel 65's \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" For New Single \"Sugar\" |publisher=About40.com |accessdate=2014-05-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505003217/http://top40.about.com/b/2009/03/09/flo-rida-digs-out-eiffel-65s-blue-da-ba-dee-for-new-single-sugar.htm# |archive-date=2014-05-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Electronic dance music|Dance music]] act [[Michael Mind Project]] used a sample of \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" in their 2012 single \"[[Feeling So Blue]]\". The single featuring [[Dante Thomas]] charted in Germany, Austria, Switzerland and France.<ref>[https://austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Michael+Mind+Project+feat.+Dante+Thomas&titel=Feeling+So+Blue&cat=s AustrianCharts.at: Michael Mind Project feat. Dante Thomas - \"Feeling So Blue\"]</ref> The American country singer [[Coffey Anderson]] sampled from the song in his 2017 release \"Bud Light Blue\" also appearing in his 2018 album ''Country Style''.\n\n==Use in media==\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2018}}\nThe song has appeared in multiple films and television series. It was included in films such as ''[[Loser (film)|Loser]]''  (2000), ''[[Big Fat Liar]]'' (2002), ''[[Iron Man 3]]'' (2013), ''[[Mommy (2014 film)|Mommy]]'' (2014), ''[[Smurfs: The Lost Village]]'' (2017), and ''[[Smallfoot (film)|Smallfoot]]'' (2018), the third instance during a [[flashback (narrative)|flashback]] scene set in 1999, the year the song became popular.<ref>{{cite AV media |people= |year=2013 |title=[[Iron Man 3]] |medium=Motion picture |format= |time= |publisher=[[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]] |location= }}</ref> In television, it was used in ''[[Daria]]'' episode [[List of Daria episodes#Season 4 (2000)|The F Word]] and in ''[[90210 (TV series)|90210]]'' finale of [[90210 (season 1)|season 1]]. On 15 March 2011 Ozone Entertainment released the song through the [[Rock Band Network]]. It is the first song on the service to incorporate the keyboard introduced in ''[[Rock Band 3]]''.<ref>[http://www.rockband.com/songs/UGC_5005633 Blue (Da Ba Dee) by Eiffel 65 // Songs // Rock Band] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319205336/http://www.rockband.com/songs/UGC_5005633 |date=March 19, 2011 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.rockband.com/blog/first-rbn-2-song First RBN 2.0 Song in the Store \u2013 \u201cBlue\u201d // Blog // Rock Band] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319093921/http://www.rockband.com/blog/first-rbn-2-song |date=March 19, 2011 }}</ref> The song was also featured in an [[EDF Energy]] advertisement in 2015.\n\nThe game ''Sir!  I'd Like To Report A Bug!'' dedicates one level to this song, in which the entire environment is colored blue.<ref>{{cite web |title=''Sir! I'd Like To Report A Bug!'' Steam store listing |url=https://store.steampowered.com/app/393240/Sir_Id_Like_To_Report_A_Bug/ |website=[[Steam (software)|Steam]] |publisher=Lord Puggington Games |accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n; Italy CD single 1999\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(DJ Ponte Ice Pop Mix)}} \u2013 6:25\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(DJ Ponte Radio Edit)}} \u2013 4:43\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Glamour Jump Mix)}} \u2013 5:19\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Dub Mix)}} \u2013 4:47\n; German CD maxi-single\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Blue Ice Pop Radio Edit)}} \u2013 3:39\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(DJ Ponte Ice Pop Mix)}} \u2013 6:26\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Hannover Remix)}} \u2013 6:24\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Dub Mix)}} \u2013 4:48\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Ice Pop Instrumental Mix)}} \u2013 6:27\n# \"Blue (Da Ba Dee)\" {{small|(Blue Paris Remix)}} \u2013 7:42\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Chart (1999\u20132000)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=Eiffel 65|song=Blue (Da Ba Dee)|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|1|artist=Eiffel 65|song=Blue (Da Ba Dee)|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|1|artist=Eiffel 65|song=Blue (Da Ba Dee)|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|2|artist=Eiffel 65|song=Blue (Da Ba Dee)|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada ([[Canadian Singles Chart|Nielsen SoundScan]])<ref name=\"Billboard\">Billboard [{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p396002|pure_url=yes}} allmusic.com] (Retrieved December 12, 2008)</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Dance (''[[Canadian dance chart|RPM]]'')<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.9972&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=j86d3uqb5jajlou8j8ag1r4lv4# |title=Canadian dance peak |access-date=2012-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226234841/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.9972&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=j86d3uqb5jajlou8j8ag1r4lv4# |archive-date=2015-12-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'')<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&fil